external_knowledge:
- A "county" refers to a geographic and administrative region within a state, often providing local government services; 
- COVID-19 is a viral respiratory disease caused by SARS-CoV-2, first identified in 2019; 
- Vaccination rate refers to the percentage of the population that has received a vaccine against a specific disease, in this case, COVID-19;
- Health insurance coverage refers to the percentage of the population that has health insurance, which helps pay for medical expenses;
- Law enforcement personnel and budget refer to the individuals employed and the financial resources allocated to enforce laws and maintain order in a county.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS TotalCounties
FROM counties
WHERE Population > 500000;
